page.title: 03Around Skipwith Common
page.content: As with most birdwatching and wildlife sites, what one sees depends largely on being at the right place at the right time. To see the Common's wide variety of birdlife would involve several visits spaced over the year and a large helping of good luck! However, even the casual visitor would be aware of the rich birdlife, unless he walked through the Common in Summer-then, insect bites would be uppermost in his mind! The full range of species appears in many birdwatching journals. The Common is particularly renowned for its colonies of black-headed gulls. The nature lover may also enjoy the wide variety of trees, plants and fungi which grow in abundance. The large Fly Agaric Toadstool is another interesting feature but beware-it's poisonous!
